section.para:
				Redefine the A4J.AJAX.onExpired method to handle the expiration of a user's session, as shown in .

					Example session expiration error

A4J.AJAX.onExpired = function(loc, expiredMsg){
    if(window.confirm("Custom onExpired handler "+expiredMsg+" for a location: "+loc)){
        return loc;
    } else {
        return false;
    }
}


				The function accepts two parameters:


						loc



								The URL of the current page, which can be updated on demand.




						expiredMsg



								A default message for the session expiration error.
